PlatformIO Unity testing:
```
project/
├── lib/
│   └── mylib/
│       ├── mylib.h
│       └── mylib.cpp
├── test/
│   ├── test_native/        # runs on host PC
│   │   └── test_math.cpp
│   └── test_embedded/      # runs on target board
│       └── test_gpio.cpp
└── platformio.ini
```

test/test_native/test_math.cpp:
```c
#include <unity.h>
#include "mylib.h"

void test_add(void) {
    TEST_ASSERT_EQUAL(5, add(2, 3));
}

void test_multiply(void) {
    TEST_ASSERT_EQUAL(6, multiply(2, 3));
}

int main(int argc, char **argv) {
    UNITY_BEGIN();
    RUN_TEST(test_add);
    RUN_TEST(test_multiply);
    return UNITY_END();
}
```

Run: `pio test -e native` (host), `pio test -e blackpill` (on-target via serial). Add `test_filter = test_native` in env to limit test scope.
